<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="38" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="38">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="11" pageNumber="38">
Only one species is placed in this genus, is also recorded from Iran (
<bibRefCitation pageId="11" pageNumber="38">Bhatti et al. 2009a</bibRefCitation>
). This species is possibly more widespread in association with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tamarix" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Tamarix</taxonomicName>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="zur Strassen, R" journalOrPublisher="Die Tierwelt Deutschlands" pageId="15" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 271" title="Die terebranten Thysanopteren Europas und des Mittelmeer-Gebietes." volume="74" year="2003 a">zur Strassen 2003a</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is included in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Thripidae" genus="Anaphothrips" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Anaphothrips" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Anaphothrips</taxonomicName>
genus-group (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, LA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="14" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 76" title="Australian Thripinae of the Anaphothrips genus-group (Thysanoptera), with three new genera and thirty-three new species." volume="2042" year="2009">Mound and Masumoto 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
